HEADWORD: Goslet
<hw>Gos"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One
of several species of pygmy geese, of the genus <gen>Nettepus</gen>.
They are about the size of a teal, and inhabit Africa, India, and
Australia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gosling</ent>⟦br⟧
